# Splice v3

Adobe Premiere Pro UXP plugin with AI-powered video editing features including clip selection, scene detection, smart cut suggestions, and audio analysis.

## Project Structure

```
src/
  ├── components/
  │   ├── panels/        # Main plugin panels (PluginApp)
  │   └── common/        # Reusable UI (Header, SelectionPanel, AIToolsPanel, SettingsPanel)
  ├── types/             # TypeScript definitions (plugin, api, premiere, ui)
  ├── utils/
  │   ├── api/           # External integrations (premiere, ai-service, plugin)
  │   └── helpers/       # Pure functions (formatters, validators)
  ├── styles/            # Global CSS and Spectrum theming
  └── index.ts           # Entry point

tests/
  ├── unit/              # Vitest unit tests
  ├── e2e/               # Playwright e2e tests
  └── __mocks__/         # UXP/Photoshop mocks

public/
  ├── manifest.json      # UXP plugin manifest
  └── icons/             # Plugin icons
```

## Tech Stack

- **UI**: Lit 3.2 + Spectrum Web Components
- **Build**: Vite 6 + TypeScript 5.7
- **Testing**: Vitest + Playwright
- **Quality**: ESLint 9 + Prettier

## Organization Rules

**Keep code organized and modularized:**
- Components → `src/components/`, one component per file
- API integrations → `src/utils/api/`
- Pure helpers → `src/utils/helpers/`
- Types → `src/types/`, grouped by domain
- Tests → `tests/unit/` and `tests/e2e/`

**Modularity principles:**
- Single responsibility per file
- Clear, descriptive file names
- Group related functionality together

## Code Quality - Zero Tolerance

After editing ANY file, run:

```bash
npm run lint
npm run typecheck
```

Fix ALL errors/warnings before continuing.

## Path Aliases

```
@/*           → src/*
@components/* → src/components/*
@utils/*      → src/utils/*
@types/*      → src/types/*
```

## UXP Development

```bash
npm run dev          # Start Vite dev server
npm run uxp:load     # Load plugin in Premiere Pro
npm run uxp:reload   # Reload after changes
npm run uxp:debug    # Debug mode
```
